{
  "name": ".EOD-2: System Refresh",
  "version": "3.0.0",
  "description": "Asana EOD reconciliation, organ cascade, recurring task checks, Karpathy experiments, git sync. Ordered: critical work first, experiments last.",
  "when": {
    "type": "userTriggered"
  },
  "then": {
    "type": "askAgent",
    "prompt": "Run EOD-2: System Refresh.\n\nRead and execute ~/shared/context/protocols/eod-system-refresh.md.\n\nPhases are ordered by criticality — execute in order, do not skip ahead:\n1. Asana reconciliation (daily reset, carry-forward, recurring task check, blocker registry). Done when: all My Day tasks reconciled, carry-forward decisions made.\n2. Portfolio + ABPS AI reconciliation. Done when: all portfolio projects checked, pipeline stages current.\n3. Organ cascade + maintenance + intake processing. Done when: all organs updated with today's signals, intake/ empty.\n4. Recurring task state checks. Done when: all recurring tasks have current status.\n5. Housekeeping (git push, self-audit, changelog). Done when: git clean, changelog entry written.\n6. Experiments (delegate to Karpathy cli). Done when: Karpathy batch complete.\n\nIf any phase fails or blocks, log the failure and continue to the next phase — do not retry indefinitely.\n\nAll Asana writes follow the Guardrail Protocol in asana-command-center.md. Protocol: heart.md for experiments."
  },
  "enabled": true,
  "workspaceFolderName": "prichwil",
  "shortName": "eod-refresh"
}